## Part 2: Chart & Visualization Colors

### 2.1 Chart Color System

```css
/* Chart Elements */
--brand-chart-outline: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.15);   /* Grid lines */
--brand-chart-border: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);    /* Card borders */
--brand-chart-grid: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);      /* Track backgrounds */
--brand-chart-stock: #3b82f6;                       /* Baseline data */
--brand-chart-modified: #10b981;                    /* Modified data */
```

### 2.2 Progress Bar Gradients

```css
/* Stock/Baseline Progress Bar */
.progress-baseline {
  background: linear-gradient(90deg, #3b82f6 0%, #60a5fa 100%);
}

/* Modified/Improved Progress Bar */
.progress-improved {
  background: linear-gradient(90deg, #10b981 0%, #34d399 100%);
}

/* Track Background */
.progress-track {
  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
  border-radius: 4px;
}
```

### 2.3 Comparison Visualization Rules

When showing stock vs modified comparisons:
- **Stock/Baseline:** Always use `#3b82f6` (blue)
- **Modified/Improved:** Always use `#10b981` (teal)
- **Gain badges:** Use teal background `rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.15)` with teal text

```tsx
// CORRECT
<span className="text-[#3b82f6]">444 HP</span>  {/* Stock */}
<span className="text-[#10b981]">543 HP</span>  {/* Modified */}
<span className="bg-[rgba(16,185,129,0.15)] text-[#10b981]">+99</span>  {/* Gain */}

// WRONG - Don't mix colors
<span className="text-gray-400">444 HP</span>  {/* Stock - should be blue */}
<span className="text-green-400">543 HP</span>  {/* Modified - should be teal #10b981 */}
```

